Text: We started this week with our client meeting as usual.
Showing the current state of the project and seeking feedback.

I was able to finish implementing the function that updates union and non-union members into a pending status to have their MECA scales updated, as well as the function that implements the pending results to the active values.
The SDHB staff were blown away by this as it basically cuts a few weeks worth of work down to a few button clicks.

We talked with them and mentioned that with our limited time left that we wouldn't be able to complete all of the functionalities to make this work but at this point we are fairly invested in the project and we can see how much of a difference it will make for them so we all agreed to keep working on it even though we have no academic obligation to.

Over the course of the week I worked on the pending changes some more, setting up a way to track changes that had been confirmed, I also worked on the team editing page, allowing doctors to be added and removed from a team from this view and also automatically adjusting their on call hours and setting up a pending value for that.
Also as a group we overhauled the UI using a UI package that has nicer looking user controls.
Looking back over this whole process, I think this is the project that I have enjoyed the most and had the most successful teamwork.
Although we did butt heads at times over how to approach certain challenges we talked them out as a team to find a resolution that everyone was happy with.
We all did our fair share and I think the end (but not quite finished) result turned out quite well.
It probably would have been beneficial to do more research into UI frameworks and figure out how to use MVVM within WPF properly.
It would have been easier for us to learn MVVM started with a small project or use more incremental development of the UI rather than build up the UI and then try make MVVM match that.
I do feel like our MVVM classes probably could have been set up better to make the whole process a lot less complicated but we did manage to make what we had work.

As for future work, I estimate that it will take us another week or 2 to finish off what is left, which is: Make sure all of the inserting, editing and removing functions work correctlyMake sure all of the calculated values are correctAdjust the report to include the current REM and the proposed REM scheduleUser testing and presentationTry find some way to speed up the loading times while using the database although not a huge issue, it's a nice to have
